<subSubSection pageId="791" pageNumber="792" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="791" pageNumber="792">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="791" pageNumber="792">
Worldwide, with about 4,260 species arrayed in 237 genera (Lorenz 2005: 453-502, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1883" genus="Nemotarsina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Nemotarsina</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="tribe" tribe="Lebiini">Lebiini</taxonomicName>
). The North American fauna is underrepresented both in term of species (about 155 species or 3.6% of the world fauna) and genera (25 genera or 10.5%). The lebiine genera are classified into the following 17 subtribes: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1871" genus="Actenonycina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Actenonycina</taxonomicName>
(one New Zealand species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" genus="Agrina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Agrina</taxonomicName>
(about 585 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1983" genus="Apenina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Apenina</taxonomicName>
(about 115 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1873" genus="Calleidina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Calleidina</taxonomicName>
(about 660 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Habu" authorityYear="1982" genus="Celaenephina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Celaenephina</taxonomicName>
(two species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte" authorityYear="1834" genus="Cymindidina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Cymindidina</taxonomicName>
(about 315 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1886" genus="Demetriadina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Demetriadina</taxonomicName>
(14 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Dromiusina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Dromiusina</taxonomicName>
(about 735 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1872" genus="Gallerucidiina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Gallerucidiina</taxonomicName>
(ten species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" genus="Lebiina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Lebiina</taxonomicName>
(about 800 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Basilewsky" authorityYear="1984" genus="Metallicina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Metallicina</taxonomicName>
(about 70 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1883" genus="Nemotarsina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Nemotarsina</taxonomicName>
(nine species), 
<taxonomicName genus="Peliocypadina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Peliocypadina</taxonomicName>
(about 70 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericalina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pericalina</taxonomicName>
(about 825 species), 
<taxonomicName genus="Physoderina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Physoderina</taxonomicName>
(45 species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Habu" authorityYear="1975" genus="Sugimotoina" lsidName="" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" rank="genus">Sugimotoina</taxonomicName>
(one species), and 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Hybotidae" genus="Trichina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="791" pageNumber="792" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trichina</taxonomicName>
(five species).
</paragraph>
